In traditional Chinese culture, the sika deer is a symbol of good luck and longevity. It is beloved by the Chinese. However, in recent years, the population in the wild has declined dramatically, making it harder to take an up-close look at them in the mountains. However, the Aba Tibetan and Qiang Autonomous Prefecture is the perfect place to encounter this rare species. About 'Journeys in Nature': Aba series: Located on the southeastern edge of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Aba Prefecture is rich inÂ diverse ecosystems, such as forests, grasslands, wetlands and glaciers. Stay tuned and explore this hidden land. More on the Aba series: Aba Series | Episode 1: Dagu glacier Aba Series | Episode 3: Baby cranes Aba Series | Episode 4: Fairy lake Aba Series | Episode 5: Zogye wetland Aba Series | Episode 6: A joyful land Aba Series | Episode 7: Nyanpo Yutse (Cover image a screenshot from the video) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)